At 01:21 PM 3/15/2003, Wakanska wrote:
>He also installed little ports on the valve covers for ducting gases to a
>breather, because he said that pressures could build under those valve
>covers, and that they needed to be equalized. Any thoughts on this?

Yeah.  Not necessary if your engine is in decent shape.  The pressure can't build under the covers, because they are connected to the crankcase through the pushrod tubes!!  Venting through your breather box will take care of everything, since that leads directly into the crankcase.

-David
